  m_Name: Modern-E9
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  mIntroMessage: Industrial change reshaped <CityName> with new technologies, expanding
    factories, and rapid population growth. Political movements challenged old systems,
    while global trade raised both opportunity and risk. Innovation accelerated faster
    than society adapted, and <CityName> had to balance progress with stability as
    it confronted competition, unrest, and evolving expectations from its citizens.
  mActionMessage: "Disputes between factory owners and workers intensified as wages,
    hours, and safety standards became points of contention. Strikes and marches
    hinted at deeper unrest beneath the city\u2019s industrious fa\xE7ade."
  mProcessedActionMessage: 
  mOutcomeType: Negative
  mOptionMessages:
  - invited worker representatives and factory owners to mediate grievances.
  - increased city watch patrols around major industrial districts.
  - introduced temporary wage adjustments to calm the unrest.
  - commissioned an independent investigation into factory safety.
  - restricted large labour gatherings to prevent escalation.
  mProcessedOptionMessages: []
  mOutcomeMessages:
  - The mediation brought both sides to a fair compromise, improving wages and safety
    conditions. Tensions eased, and many workers returned to their posts with renewed
    trust.
  - Talks collapsed as both parties refused to yield. The failed negotiations deepened
    hostilities, sparking larger strikes and halting production across several districts.
  - The added patrols prevented clashes and protected both workers and property.
    The visible security helped maintain order while deeper issues were addressed.
  - The heavy patrol presence was seen as intimidation, provoking anger among workers.
    Confrontations broke out, and unrest spread more rapidly than before.
  - "The wage increases relieved immediate frustrations, and many workers paused
    their strikes. Factories resumed operations, stabilising <CityName>\u2019s economy."
  - Workers viewed the adjustments as shallow appeasement. Demands escalated, and
    resentment grew when wages fell again after the temporary period ended.
  - The investigation exposed hazardous conditions and led to meaningful reforms.
    Workers felt vindicated, and factory owners earned new respect for addressing
    the findings.
  - The investigation angered several factory owners, who saw it as an attack on
    their businesses. They retaliated by reducing hours or laying off workers, inflaming
    tensions further.
  - The restrictions curbed mass unrest long enough for dialogue to resume. With
    time to cool, several factions reconsidered more peaceful negotiation.
  - The restrictions were seen as a suppression of worker rights, prompting secret
    meetings and underground organising. The movement grew more radical and harder
    to control.
